VALUES
(19, 119, 142, 142, 'kjv', 'Thy righteousness is an everlasting righteousness', 0, 49, 'greek', 'Understanding ''Righteousness''', 'צדק (tsedeq, H6664) - righteousness, justice, rightness. This Hebrew term signifies not just moral uprightness but also the fulfillment of God’s covenantal obligations. It emphasizes that God''s righteousness is integral to His character and unchanging across generations.', 'textformat.abc', '[{"type": "strongs", "reference": "H6664", "description": "Strong''s number for ''righteousness''"}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 142, 142, 'kjv', 'thy law is the truth', 55, 75, 'question', 'Application of God''s Law', 'How do we live out the truth of God''s law in our daily lives? In what specific ways can we align our actions with the principles outlined in Scripture, reflecting the truth that God’s law is not just a set of rules but a guide to living in accordance with His will?', 'questionmark.circle.fill', NULL, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 143, 143, 'kjv', 'Trouble and anguish have taken hold on me', 0, 41, 'connection', 'Affliction in Scripture', 'This phrase resonates with Psalm 34:19, which states, ''Many are the afflictions of the righteous, but the Lord delivers him out of them all.'' Both verses highlight the reality of suffering in the life of a believer, yet emphasize God''s faithfulness in providing comfort and deliverance. This connection deepens our understanding of how God''s commandments can offer solace amidst life''s struggles.', 'link', '[{"type": "crossReference", "reference": "Psalm 34:19", "description": "Highlights the theme of affliction and God''s deliverance."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 143, 143, 'kjv', 'yet thy commandments are my delights', 43, 79, 'theology', 'Joy in Obedience', 'This passage suggests that true joy and delight can be found in adherence to God''s commandments, reflecting a profound theological principle that obedience leads to spiritual fulfillment. Many scholars believe this aligns with Jesus'' teaching in John 15:10-11, where He states that obeying His commands results in joy being complete. This reinforces the idea that God''s laws are not burdensome but are intended for our good and happiness.', 'sparkles', NULL, 'standard', true, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 143, 143, 'kjv', 'Trouble and anguish have taken hold on me', 0, 41, 'question', 'Finding Delight in Commandments', 'In times of trouble, how can focusing on God''s commandments transform our perspective on our circumstances? What specific commandments can we meditate on that provide comfort and strength in our moments of anguish?', 'questionmark.circle.fill', NULL, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 143, 143, 'kjv', 'yet thy commandments are my delights', 43, 79, 'greek', 'Delight in Commandments', 'שָׁעַשַׁע (sha''ashuim, H8181) - delights, joy. This Hebrew term conveys a sense of deep pleasure and satisfaction found in God''s laws, emphasizing that obedience is not merely duty but a source of joy. Understanding this term enriches our appreciation for the relationship between love for God''s law and the joy it can bring.', 'textformat.abc', '[{"type": "strongs", "reference": "H8181", "description": "Strong''s number for the Hebrew term ''sha''ashuim'' meaning delights."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 144, 144, 'kjv', 'The righteousness of thy testimonies is everlasting', 0, 51, 'connection', 'Eternal Righteousness', 'This phrase connects to Psalm 119:160, which states, ''Thy word is true from the beginning: and every one of thy righteous judgments endureth forever.'' Both verses emphasize the enduring nature of God''s righteousness and truth. This consistency reinforces the believer''s trust in God''s character and His commandments.', 'link', '[{"type": "crossReference", "reference": "Psalm 119:160", "description": "Highlights the eternal aspect of God''s word."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 144, 144, 'kjv', 'give me understanding, and I shall live', 53, 92, 'theology', 'Understanding and Life', 'Many scholars believe that this plea for understanding reflects the biblical principle that true life comes from knowing and obeying God''s laws. This aligns with John 17:3, where eternal life is defined as knowing God. Thus, understanding His testimonies is not merely intellectual but vital for spiritual vitality.', 'sparkles', '[{"type": "crossReference", "reference": "John 17:3", "description": "Defines eternal life as knowing God."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', true, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 144, 144, 'kjv', 'give me understanding', 53, 74, 'question', 'Seeking Divine Insight', 'What does it mean to actively seek understanding from God in your daily life? In what ways can you align your pursuits with His testimonies to gain deeper insights into your circumstances?', 'lightbulb', NULL, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 144, 144, 'kjv', 'The righteousness of thy testimonies is everlasting', 0, 51, 'greek', 'Key Concept in Greek', 'δικαιοσύνη (dikaiosynē, G1343) - righteousness, justice. This term captures the essence of God''s moral character as the standard for ethical behavior, stressing that His judgments are not arbitrary but rooted in His eternal righteousness.', 'character.book.closed', '[{"type": "strongs", "reference": "G1343", "description": "Strong''s number for ''righteousness.''"}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 145, 145, 'kjv', 'I cried with my whole heart;', 0, 28, 'question', 'Whole Hearted Cry', 'What does it mean to cry out to God with one''s whole heart? How does this depth of emotion reflect the sincerity of our prayers and our relationship with God?', 'questionmark.circle.fill', NULL, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 145, 145, 'kjv', 'hear me, O Lord:', 29, 45, 'theology', 'God''s Listening Ear', 'This plea emphasizes the relational aspect of prayer in the faith tradition. Many scholars believe that the act of crying out signifies a deep trust in God''s willingness to respond, aligning with biblical teachings on prayer found in James 5:16, which states that the prayer of a righteous person is powerful and effective.', 'person.2.fill', '[{"type": "crossReference", "reference": "James 5:16", "description": "This verse highlights the power of prayer and God''s responsiveness."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', true, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 145, 145, 'kjv', 'I will keep thy statutes.', 46, 71, 'connection', 'Commitment to God''s Word', 'This commitment resonates with Psalm 1:2, where delight in the law of the Lord leads to fruitfulness. The connection emphasizes that a heart aligned with God’s commandments is foundational to spiritual vitality and obedience, illustrating a holistic approach to faith.', 'link', '[{"type": "crossReference", "reference": "Psalm 1:2", "description": "This verse connects the joy of following God''s law with overall well-being."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 146, 146, 'kjv', 'I cried unto thee; save me,', 0, 27, 'connection', 'Call for Salvation', 'This phrase echoes Psalm 34:17, ''The righteous cry, and the Lord heareth, and delivereth them out of all their troubles.'' Both verses emphasize the believer’s reliance on God for salvation and deliverance, highlighting the intimate relationship between prayer and divine intervention. This connection reinforces the assurance that God hears and responds to the cries of His people.', 'link', '[{"type": "crossReference", "reference": "Psalm 34:17", "description": "Illustrates God\u2019s faithfulness in responding to the cries of the righteous."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 146, 146, 'kjv', 'I cried unto thee; save me,', 0, 27, 'theology', 'Dependence on God', 'This passage suggests the theological concept of grace and dependence on God for salvation. Many scholars believe that the act of crying out for salvation reflects a posture of humility and recognition of human inability to save oneself. It underscores the foundational Christian teaching that salvation is a gift from God, not a result of human effort.', 'person.2.fill', '[{"type": "commentary", "reference": "Matthew Henry''s Commentary", "description": "Discusses the importance of reliance on God in times of distress."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', true, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 146, 146, 'kjv', 'I shall keep thy testimonies.', 32, 61, 'question', 'Commitment to Obedience', 'What does it mean to keep God’s testimonies in the context of receiving salvation? How does understanding our need for God’s help shape our commitment to live according to His Word? Reflecting on this can help us consider how gratitude for salvation influences our daily choices and obedience to God’s commands.', 'questionmark.circle.fill', NULL, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 146, 146, 'kjv', 'save me, and I shall keep thy testimonies.', 19, 61, 'greek', 'Key Terms in Salvation', 'σώζω (sōzō, G4982) - to save, to deliver, to heal. This term emphasizes the comprehensive nature of salvation that encompasses physical, spiritual, and emotional aspects. The plea for salvation is not just for deliverance from danger but also implies a desire for restoration and wholeness in following God’s ways.', 'textformat.abc', '[{"type": "strongs", "reference": "G4982", "description": "Strong''s number for the Greek term meaning to save or heal."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 147, 147, 'kjv', 'I prevented the dawning of the morning', 0, 38, 'connection', 'Early Seeking of God', 'This phrase echoes the sentiment found in Lamentations 3:22-23, where the steadfast love of the Lord is emphasized each morning. The connection highlights the importance of seeking God first thing in the day, mirroring the psalmist''s deep longing and commitment to prayer at dawn. Both passages emphasize renewal and hope found in God''s faithfulness.', 'link', '[{"type": "crossReference", "reference": "Lamentations 3:22-23", "description": "Emphasizes God''s faithfulness every morning."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 147, 147, 'kjv', 'I hoped in thy word', 51, 70, 'greek', 'Significance of ''Word''', 'λόγος (logos, G3056) - word, reason, discourse. In this context, ''logos'' conveys the idea of God''s revealed truth and promises. The psalmist''s hope is anchored in God''s word, which serves as a foundation for faith and guidance. Understanding ''logos'' helps illustrate the transformative power of Scripture in the believer''s life.', 'textformat.abc', '[{"type": "strongs", "reference": "G3056", "description": "Strong''s number for the Greek term."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 147, 147, 'kjv', 'I hoped in thy word', 51, 70, 'theology', 'Hope in Scripture', 'This passage suggests that true hope is found in the promises of God as revealed in Scripture. Many scholars believe this reflects a foundational Christian teaching that faith is not merely a feeling but is rooted in God''s character and His written word. This highlights the importance of Scripture in nurturing spiritual resilience.', 'sparkles', '[{"type": "commentary", "reference": "John Gill''s Exposition of the Bible", "description": "Discusses the significance of hope in God''s promises."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', true, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 147, 147, 'kjv', 'I prevented the dawning of the morning', 0, 38, 'question', 'Morning Devotion Reflection', 'What practices can you incorporate into your mornings to ensure that your first thoughts are directed toward God and His word? How might this shape your day in terms of faith and perspective?', 'lightbulb', NULL, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 148, 148, 'kjv', 'Mine eyes prevent the night watches,', 0, 36, 'theology', 'Spiritual Vigilance', 'This phrase reflects the theme of spiritual vigilance and the priority of seeking God. The psalmist expresses a commitment to remain alert and engaged in prayer and meditation during the night, which symbolizes a time of darkness and temptation. Many scholars believe this underscores the importance of being spiritually awake in times of trial, as seen in 1 Thessalonians 5:6, which encourages believers to be sober and alert.', 'person.2.fill', '[{"type": "commentary", "reference": "1 Thessalonians 5:6", "description": "Encourages spiritual alertness among believers."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 148, 148, 'kjv', 'that I might meditate in thy word.', 37, 71, 'connection', 'Meditation in Scripture', 'The act of meditation on God''s word is a central theme in Scripture. This verse connects well with Joshua 1:8, where God commands Joshua to meditate on the law day and night for success. This connection highlights the transformative power of Scripture and its role in guiding one''s life and decisions. Meditation is not merely reading but involves deep reflection and application.', 'link', '[{"type": "crossReference", "reference": "Joshua 1:8", "description": "God''s command to meditate on His law for success."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 148, 148, 'kjv', 'Mine eyes prevent the night watches,', 0, 36, 'greek', 'Meditation (הָגָה)', 'הָגָה (hāgāh, H1897) - to meditate, muse, or ponder. This Hebrew term suggests a deep, reflective thought process that involves vocalization or muttering, indicating that meditation on God''s word is an active, engaging practice rather than passive reading. This aligns with the psalmist''s intent to immerse himself in Scripture during the night watches.', 'textformat.abc', '[{"type": "strongs", "reference": "H1897", "description": "Strong''s number for ''to meditate.''"}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 148, 148, 'kjv', 'that I might meditate in thy word.', 37, 71, 'question', 'Reflecting on Meditation', 'How does prioritizing meditation on God''s word during challenging times change your approach to life''s difficulties? What practices can you adopt to ensure that God''s word guides your thoughts and actions?', 'lightbulb', NULL, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 149, 149, 'kjv', 'Hear my voice according unto thy lovingkindness:', 0, 48, 'connection', 'God''s Lovingkindness', 'This phrase echoes Psalm 25:6, where the psalmist similarly appeals to God''s mercy. It highlights the intimate relationship between the believer and God, emphasizing that requests for guidance and help are rooted in God’s character. Understanding God''s lovingkindness is crucial to grasp the nature of His responses to our cries for help.', 'link', '[{"type": "crossReference", "reference": "Psalm 25:6", "description": "Both verses reflect an appeal to God''s mercy."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 149, 149, 'kjv', 'quicken me according to thy judgment.', 57, 94, 'theology', 'Spiritual Revitalization', 'The request to be ''quicken[ed]'' points to the theological concept of spiritual revitalization, which is often associated with God''s grace enabling believers to live righteously. Many scholars believe this reflects the transformative power of God''s judgment, where His decisions lead not only to correction but also to a new life in obedience and faith.', 'sparkles', '[{"type": "commentary", "reference": "Matthew Henry''s Commentary", "description": "Discusses the role of God''s judgment in renewing the believer."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', true, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 149, 149, 'kjv', 'O Lord, quicken me according to thy judgment.', 49, 94, 'question', 'Seeking Renewal', 'How does understanding God''s judgment as a source of life and renewal change your perspective on personal struggles? In what ways can you actively seek God''s revitalization through His word and commandments?', 'lightbulb', NULL, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 149, 149, 'kjv', 'according unto thy lovingkindness:', 14, 48, 'greek', 'Lovingkindness in Hebrew', 'חֶסֶד (chesed, H2617) - lovingkindness, mercy, steadfast love. This term signifies a deep, covenantal love that reflects God''s faithfulness. Its inclusion in the plea underscores the believer''s reliance on God''s character as the basis for receiving help.', 'textformat.abc', '[{"type": "strongs", "reference": "H2617", "description": "Defines the term used for lovingkindness."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 150, 150, 'kjv', 'They draw nigh that follow after mischief:', 0, 42, 'connection', 'Connection to Evil Pursuits', 'This phrase evokes James 4:8, which states, ''Draw near to God, and He will draw near to you.'' The contrast between drawing near to God and pursuing mischief highlights the spiritual distance created by sin. It underscores the importance of intentionality in our relationships with God versus the distractions of wrongdoing.', 'link', '[{"type": "crossReference", "reference": "James 4:8", "description": "Emphasizes the need for closeness to God as opposed to mischief."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 150, 150, 'kjv', 'they are far from thy law.', 43, 69, 'theology', 'Separation from God''s Law', 'This passage suggests a fundamental theological principle: distance from God''s law equates to separation from His presence and guidance. Many scholars believe that adherence to God''s commandments fosters a deeper relationship with Him, while rebellion leads to spiritual alienation. This is reflected in the broader biblical theme of the covenant relationship between God and His people.', 'person.2.fill', NULL, 'standard', true, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 150, 150, 'kjv', 'They draw nigh that follow after mischief:', 0, 42, 'question', 'Reflecting on Misguided Pursuits', 'What kinds of mischief might distract you from drawing near to God? In what ways can you actively choose to pursue righteousness instead of the fleeting allure of wrongdoing?', 'questionmark.circle.fill', NULL, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 150, 150, 'kjv', 'they are far from thy law.', 43, 69, 'greek', 'Understanding ''law''', 'תּוֹרָה (torah, H8451) - law, instruction, teaching. This term signifies not just legal statutes but a holistic guide for living in accordance with God''s will, emphasizing the relational aspect of obedience.', 'textformat.abc', '[{"type": "strongs", "reference": "H8451", "description": "Represents the Hebrew understanding of law as guidance."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 151, 151, 'kjv', 'Thou art near, O Lord;', 0, 22, 'theology', 'God''s Immanence', 'This phrase emphasizes the theological concept of God''s immanence, which suggests that God is actively present and involved in the lives of His creation. Many scholars believe that this nearness implies a relational aspect of God, inviting believers to seek comfort and guidance in His presence. This idea is supported by James 4:8, which states, ''Draw near to God, and He will draw near to you.''', 'person.2.fill', '[{"type": "crossReference", "reference": "James 4:8", "description": "Illustrates the relational aspect of drawing near to God."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 151, 151, 'kjv', 'and all thy commandments are truth.', 23, 58, 'connection', 'Truth of God''s Word', 'This assertion connects to John 17:17, where Jesus says, ''Sanctify them by Your truth. Your word is truth.'' The connection underscores the foundational belief that God''s commandments are not merely rules but are rooted in absolute truth, guiding believers in their moral and spiritual lives. Recognizing God''s commandments as truth encourages a deeper commitment to living according to His will.', 'link', '[{"type": "crossReference", "reference": "John 17:17", "description": "Affirms the truthfulness of God''s word."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 151, 151, 'kjv', 'Thou art near, O Lord;', 0, 22, 'question', 'Reflecting on God''s Presence', 'What does it mean to you personally that ''Thou art near, O Lord''? How can this understanding influence your daily decisions and interactions with others? Reflect on how the nearness of God can provide strength in times of trouble and guidance in moments of uncertainty.', 'questionmark.circle.fill', NULL, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 151, 151, 'kjv', 'all thy commandments are truth.', 27, 58, 'greek', 'Understanding ''Truth''', 'ἀλήθεια (aletheia, G225) - truth, reality, sincerity. This Greek term emphasizes not just factual correctness but also the idea of authenticity and faithfulness. In the context of God''s commandments, it signifies that His laws reflect the ultimate reality and are trustworthy guides for living.', 'textformat.abc', '[{"type": "strongs", "reference": "G225", "description": "Strong''s number for the Greek word ''aletheia''."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 152, 152, 'kjv', 'Concerning thy testimonies', 0, 26, 'connection', 'Testimonies in Scripture', 'This phrase echoes the importance of God''s testimonies throughout Scripture. For instance, Psalm 19:7 states, ''The law of the Lord is perfect, converting the soul: the testimony of the Lord is sure, making wise the simple.'' This highlights the enduring nature of God''s commandments, linking this verse to the idea of divine truth and guidance.', 'link', '[{"type": "crossReference", "reference": "Psalm 19:7", "description": "Shows the significance of God''s testimonies."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 152, 152, 'kjv', 'I have known of old', 28, 47, 'theology', 'Eternal Truths', 'Many scholars believe that the phrase ''I have known of old'' reflects the timeless nature of God''s word. This suggests that God''s testimonies are not just historical artifacts but ongoing truths that have been recognized by believers throughout generations. This perspective reinforces the doctrine of the immutability of God''s character.', 'sparkles', NULL, 'standard', true, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 152, 152, 'kjv', 'founded them for ever', 63, 84, 'greek', 'Eternal Foundation', 'ἰδρύω (idryō, G2311) - to establish, to found. This term emphasizes the permanence and stability of God''s testimonies, suggesting they are securely established and unchanging, providing a firm foundation for faith.', 'textformat.abc', '[{"type": "strongs", "reference": "G2311", "description": "Describes the concept of establishing a firm foundation."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 152, 152, 'kjv', 'founded them for ever', 63, 84, 'question', 'Understanding Permanence', 'What does it mean for God''s testimonies to be founded ''for ever''? How does this assurance influence your trust in His promises and commands today?', 'lightbulb', NULL, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 153, 153, 'kjv', 'Consider mine affliction, and deliver me: for I do not forget thy law.', 0, 70, 'connection', 'Affliction and Deliverance', 'This verse resonates with Psalm 34:17-19, which states, ''The righteous cry, and the Lord hears, and delivers them out of all their troubles.'' The connection emphasizes that God is attentive to the afflictions of His people and acts to deliver them, affirming that remembering His law is crucial in times of distress.', 'link', '[{"type": "crossReference", "reference": "Psalm 34:17-19", "description": "Highlights God''s responsiveness to the righteous in their afflictions."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 153, 153, 'kjv', 'Consider mine affliction, and deliver me: for I do not forget thy law.', 0, 70, 'theology', 'Law and Affliction', 'This verse suggests a theological principle that obedience to God''s law provides a foundation for seeking His help in times of trouble. Many scholars believe that the psalmist''s remembrance of God''s law signifies a deep commitment to His commandments, which in turn invites divine intervention.', 'person.2.fill', '[{"type": "commentary", "reference": "Matthew Henry''s Commentary", "description": "Discusses the relationship between obedience to God and experiencing His deliverance."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', true, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 153, 153, 'kjv', 'Consider mine affliction, and deliver me: for I do not forget thy law.', 0, 70, 'question', 'Reflecting on Affliction', 'In what ways does our remembrance of God''s law shape our response to personal affliction? How can we actively recall His teachings when facing struggles to seek His deliverance?', 'questionmark.circle.fill', NULL, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 153, 153, 'kjv', 'Consider mine affliction, and deliver me: for I do not forget thy law.', 0, 70, 'greek', 'Affliction in Hebrew', 'עָנִי (ani, H6041) - afflicted, humble, poor. This Hebrew word indicates a state of distress that often leads individuals to seek God''s intervention. Understanding its meaning enriches our comprehension of the psalmist''s plea for deliverance.', 'textformat.abc', '[{"type": "strongs", "reference": "H6041", "description": "Strong''s number for the Hebrew term related to affliction."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 154, 154, 'kjv', 'Plead my cause, and deliver me:', 0, 31, 'connection', 'Divine Advocacy', 'This phrase resonates with other scriptural instances where believers seek God''s intervention. For example, 1 John 2:1 refers to Jesus as our advocate. This connection emphasizes the importance of divine support in times of distress, suggesting that God actively engages in our personal struggles.', 'link', '[{"type": "crossReference", "reference": "1 John 2:1", "description": "Jesus as our advocate before the Father."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 154, 154, 'kjv', 'quicken me according to thy word.', 32, 65, 'greek', 'Understanding ''Quicken''', 'חָיָה (chayah, H2421) - to live, to revive. This Hebrew word emphasizes the act of bringing life or revitalization. In the context of this verse, it suggests a plea not just for deliverance but also for spiritual rejuvenation according to God''s promises.', 'textformat.abc', '[{"type": "strongs", "reference": "H2421", "description": "Strong''s number for ''quicken'' in the Old Testament."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 154, 154, 'kjv', 'Plead my cause, and deliver me:', 0, 31, 'theology', 'God''s Justice', 'This verse reflects the theological concept of God''s justice and mercy. Many scholars believe that appealing to God for justice acknowledges His role as the righteous judge who delivers His people from oppression. It underscores the belief that God is attentive to the plight of the faithful.', 'person.2.fill', '[{"type": "commentary", "reference": "Matthew Henry''s Commentary", "description": "Discussion on God''s justice and mercy in the Psalms."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', true, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 154, 154, 'kjv', 'quicken me according to thy word.', 32, 65, 'question', 'Seeking Spiritual Renewal', 'What does it mean for you to seek renewal through God''s word in your life? How can the promises within Scripture inspire revival and hope in your current circumstances?', 'lightbulb', NULL, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(19, 119, 155, 155, 'kjv', 'Salvation is far from the wicked', 0, 32, 'connection', 'Salvation and Wickedness', 'This phrase echoes the themes found in Isaiah 59:2, which states, ''But your iniquities have separated between you and your God, and your sins have hid his face from you, that he will not hear.'' The connection underscores the biblical principle that moral and spiritual disobedience distances individuals from divine grace and salvation.', 'link', '[{"type": "crossReference", "reference": "Isaiah 59:2", "description": "Highlights the separation caused by sin."}]'::jsonb, 'standard', false, 'v1.0', 'gpt-4o-mini');